\n< Serena >Ohhh!!

\n< Male >Ohhh... Ugh, so this is the body of the beautiful
princess of Venus...
\n< Serena >Ugh... Ahh...!

\n< Male >I decided from the moment I saw you. I decided
from the moment you were revealed to that
Battabayar guy.
\n< Male >I would make you mine.
\n< Male >Someday, Someday, I would do this..! Hmph!
\n< Serena >Ahhhh!
\n< Male >Hahaha! It took five years but...!

\n< Male >This place is... better than you can imagine! I'm
dying of excitement! I can't stop the blood from
coursing through my veins!

\n< Male >Are all the women in the northern region like
this?

\n< Male >This battle is already over. Once the grasslands
unite, the next step is to rampage through the
imperial territory...

\n< Male >It might be interesting to try invading the
northern region by passing through the Great
Forest this time... don't you think?
\n< Serena >Ahh... Ah...! Ugh...!
\n< Child >Eeeh...
\n< Serena >!! You...! Why did you come back...!

\n< Male >Thanks for your effort. Phew. They are all ugly,
unlike their mother. Did the blood of Batbayar
only come out strongly?

\n< Male >Hm... Is someone missing? Wasn't there an insolent
brat of a certain age?
\n< Subordinate >I'm sorry. They resisted.
\n< Serena >Ahhh...!
\n< Male >If you haven't let them escape, it doesn't matter.
\n< Male >What we do is the same anyway.
\n< Subordinate >Well then.
\n< Serena >S-Stop it!
\n< Male >Hmmm?
\n< Serena >Please... the children, at least...!

\n< Male >Those are not kid you wanted to make, is it? You
were brought in as a trophy....

\n< Serena >The childrens are innocent... They are all good
children...!

\n< Serena >The only brightness I've gained in this life of
captivity....

\n< Child >Eh...what are you doing naked...? Who is that old
man...?
\n< Serena >This is...hmm! It's...nothing...nothing...!
\n< Child >Eh? Your face is red...
\n< Serena >It's okay, it's oka...nggh!...so...!

\n< Male >Hmph. Even though they're just kids, at that age,
they should be a bit more observant.

\n< Male >It seems like the seed wasn't good. Or maybe it's
the education? He's fond of cats, right?
\n< Serena >Shut up... Shut up...!

\n< Male >Don't worry. My seed is of better quality than
Batbayar's. I'll make sure to impregnate you with
a replacement soon. Something even better.

\n< Male >If you're going to breastfeed anyway, wouldn't it
be better to have strong children made from
superior seeds?
\n< Male >Take them.
\n< Child >Ei-jiiiiiiiiiiii!!!
\n< Serena >Aaaaaahhhhh!!!

\n< Male >Look, don't cry, don't cry. This is also a custom
of the chaotic world. It's the fate of the
grasslands.
\n< Serena >Ugh!

\n< Male >Good women have the obligation to give birth to
stronger children. They have a responsibility.

\n< Male >It is a sin against our fathers to leave a weaker
generation.
\n< Serena >You...! How dare you...! How dare you...!

\n< Male >Hahaha, that's right, those eyes. The eyes of a
mother who had their child taken awayI wanted to
see those eyes of yours!

\n< Male >I'll have a replacement for you in a minute. You
just have to continue to bear my children.

\n< Male >Give birth to a horrible boy. A boy who will be
the enemy of your other childs.

\n< Male >Since it's our child, he will grow up wise and
strong. The same child will invade your homeland.
......

\n< Male >Isn't it exciting to even dream about it? Hahaha,
I'm looking forward to it. I'm really looking
forward to it...
